    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Swarm Bite (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Hive Larva surges forward, attempting to bite a target within reach. It makes a melee attack, dealing D4 Piercing damage on a hit. If the attack hits, the target must succeed on an Endurance check or take ongoing 1 Acid damage at the start of each of their turns until they receive magical healing or the combat ends. This effect is not cumulative.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Luminescent Distraction (Magical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Hive Larva emits a blinding burst of luminescence, attempting to disorient nearby creatures. All creatures within the room must succeed on an Endurance check or be Blinded until the end of their next turn as their vision is overwhelmed by the intense light.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Consume Essence (Magical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Hive Larva extend their proboscises toward a target, attempting to drain its life force. The target must succeed on an Endurance check or take D6 Necrotic damage and have their Toughness maximum reduced by the same amount until they finish a rest. The Hive Larva heals up to half the damage dealt.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>Hive Larvae are repugnant grub-like monsters, loathsome creatures with a collective hunger for all that exists. These creatures, each about the size of a cat, are covered in slimy, iridescent carapaces, pulsating with an unsettling luminescence that draws the eyes towards them. Emerging from the hidden depths of their hive, they always appear in groups, moving as one and exhibiting a hive-mind intelligence. With relentless determination, they voraciously consume everything in their path, from the roots of ancient trees to unsuspecting creatures crossing their territory.</p></div>",
